This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it focuses on natural language processing and semantic word similarity. It also involves the use of a knowledge graph, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the creation of word embeddings, which is a common topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves ranking and similarity measures. Finally, the paper also involves the use of distributional semantics, which falls under the Software Development (cs.SD) sub-category.
